@startuml seq-03-logout
title POST /auth/logout — revoke current refresh session

actor "User" as U <<human>>
participant "Browser" as B <<browser>>
participant "Express\n/auth" as API <<service>>
database "PostgreSQL" as DB

U -> B: Sign out
B -> API: POST /auth/logout\n(optional Cookie kp_rt)

API -> API: readRefreshCookie
opt Cookie present
  API -> API: hashRefreshToken
  API -> DB: refreshSession.findUnique(tokenHash)
  API -> DB: refreshSession.updateMany\nrevokedAt = now (matching hash)
  API -> DB: logAuthEvent(LOGOUT, metadata count)
end
API -> API: clearRefreshCookie(res)
API --> B: 200 { ok: true }
B -> B: Drop in-memory access token

note right of API
  Source: **apps/api/src/routes/auth.ts** (~474+).
  **POST /auth/logout-all** (authenticated) revokes\nall sessions for userId — separate flow.
end note

@enduml
